        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Akshaya Tritiya is one of the most auspicious days in the Hindu calendar, celebrated as a symbol of prosperity, good fortune, and new beginnings. The word <em>Akshaya</em> means “never diminishing,” which is why purchases made on this day are believed to bring lasting wealth and success. Families across India celebrate the festival by investing in valuable items, starting new ventures, or bringing home things that symbolize growth and abundance.</p><p>Traditionally, buying gold on Akshaya Tritiya is considered extremely lucky, but over time the list of auspicious purchases has expanded. From precious metals and jewellery to spiritual items and investments, people choose items that represent prosperity and long-term value.</p><p>If you are planning to celebrate the festival in a meaningful way, here are 11 best things to buy on Akshaya Tritiya to attract wealth and prosperity.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1. Gold Jewellery – A Timeless Symbol of Prosperity and Good Fortune",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>1. Gold Jewellery – A Timeless Symbol of Prosperity and Good Fortune</h2>",
            "custom_id": "gold",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_D9njWC": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Gold jewellery has always been the most traditional and meaningful purchase on Akshaya Tritiya. In Indian culture, gold represents wealth, purity, and prosperity, and it is closely associated with Goddess Lakshmi, the deity of fortune and abundance. Buying gold on this auspicious day is believed to invite lasting prosperity and positive energy into your home.</p><p>At<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Lucira Jewelry\"> Lucira Jewelry</a>, our gold jewellery collections are thoughtfully designed to celebrate this tradition with elegance and modern craftsmanship. Whether it’s a necklace, bracelet, ring, or pair of earrings, gold jewellery bought on Akshaya Tritiya often becomes a treasured possession that can be passed down through generations.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
