        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Diamond jewellery is another popular choice during Akshaya Tritiya for those who want to celebrate prosperity with elegance. Diamonds symbolize strength, clarity, and everlasting value, making them perfect for marking important life moments.</p><p>At Lucira Jewelry, our diamond jewellery collections feature ethically created lab grown diamonds that offer the same brilliance as mined diamonds while being environmentally responsible. Whether it’s a ring, pendant, or bracelet, Lucira’s diamond designs are crafted to celebrate prosperity with timeless sparkle.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "3. Silver Coins or Utensils – A Traditional Way to Invite Wealth and Blessings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>3. Silver Coins or Utensils – A Traditional Way to Invite Wealth and Blessings</h2>",
            "custom_id": "silver",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qwTzXx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Silver purchases are also considered highly auspicious during Akshaya Tritiya. Many families buy silver coins engraved with Goddess Lakshmi and Lord Ganesha as a symbol of prosperity and divine blessings.</p><p>Silver utensils such as plates, bowls, and puja items are also common purchases on this day. These items are often used during religious rituals and festive celebrations, making them both spiritual and practical.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
